      "id": "dm-001",
      "year": 2024,
      "question": "Which of the following is a tautology?",
      "options": {
        "A": "p ∨ ¬p",
        "B": "p ∧ ¬p",
        "C": "p → q",
        "D": "¬p ∧ p"
      },
      "correct_answer": "A",
      "explanation": "p ∨ ¬p is the Law of Excluded Middle — it is always TRUE regardless of p's truth value. p ∧ ¬p is always FALSE (contradiction). p → q depends on values of p and q.",
      "difficulty": "easy",
      "marks": 2,
      "negative_marks": -0.67,
      "tags": ["logic", "tautology"]
    },
    {
      "id": "dm-002",
      "year": 2023,
      "question": "In a group of 100 students, 60 study Maths, 50 study Physics, and 20 study both. How many study neither?",
      "options": {
        "A": "10",
        "B": "20",
        "C": "30",
        "D": "40"
      },
      "correct_answer": "A",
      "explanation": "|M ∪ P| = |M| + |P| - |M ∩ P| = 60 + 50 - 20 = 90. Neither = 100 - 90 = 10.",
      "difficulty": "easy",
      "marks": 2,
      "negative_marks": -0.67,
      "tags": ["set-theory", "inclusion-exclusion"]
    },
    {
