      "question": "Which relation on {1,2,3} is an equivalence relation?",
      "options": {
        "A": "{(1,1),(2,2),(3,3),(1,2),(2,1)}",
        "B": "{(1,2),(2,3),(1,3)}",
        "C": "{(1,1),(2,2),(1,2)}",
        "D": "{(1,2),(2,1),(2,3)}"
      },
      "correct_answer": "A",
      "explanation": "Option A: Reflexive (1,1),(2,2),(3,3) ✓; Symmetric (1,2)↔(2,1) ✓; Transitive (1,2),(2,1)→(1,1) ✓. This is an equivalence relation. Option C lacks (2,1) so not symmetric.",
      "difficulty": "medium",
      "marks": 2,
      "negative_marks": -0.67,
      "tags": ["relations", "equivalence"]
    },
